<p>The humble Pestle &amp; Mortar is probably one of mankind''s earliest innovations. Described as ''the original food processor'' the pestle and mortar were widely used in the prehistoric world. Neolithic/Bronze Age examples which have been found suggests they would have been used to crush &amp; grind herbs, spices and seeds just as they are used in kitchens today. This pestle &amp; mortar is made from marble, is top quality and quite a substantial piece! Ideal for kitchen use or simply as an ornate item for the kitchen. Approx 12cm diameter.</p>